args: In the end, Xainfried, Fydon, and Felyx got all\nof the presents delivered. Then, that night...
Taking in the yuletree, are you?
Heh. Yes, it really is a beautiful sight.
Ah, forgive meâ€”I nearly forgot I came to\ngive you this.
You did excellent work as Saint Starfall,\nso I brought you some Dragonyule cake\nas reward for your efforts.
Slow down, you'll make yourselves sick!\nThere's plenty where that came from,\nso take your time.
For a moment I thought someone was\nwatching us. Did I imagine it?
Rrgh! No, I am NOT all right, thank you\nvery much! They just charged at me\nfor no reason!
I'm sorry, I'm sure they didn't mean\nany harm.
I... D-don't worry about it.\nNow, if you'll excuse me!
You came to speak with us, right?\nYou were just waiting for a good moment.
N-no, I was just...looking at that tree!\nThat's all.
Aah! Don't startle me like that!
Sorry. I simply wished to share\na word of thanks.
Thank you for worrying about us before.\nI'm sorry I didn't realize what you were\ndoing sooner.
While we were out delivering presents,\nwe were attacked by two members of\nthe Syrol tribe.
That's what you were worried about,\nisn't it?
So you really did encounter them...
The Syrol tribe are my countrymen.\nThey share our dream of expunging\ndragons from the world.
But recklessly hunting dragons puts both\nthemselves and our country in dangerâ€”\nso I bade them remain within our borders.
Recently, however, I received word that\nthey had slipped beyond them, and were\nheading this direction.
Which is why you didn't want us leaving\nthe safety of the castle.
Yes. But I failed to convey that properly,\nand for that I am sorry.
I wanted to warn you, so Fydon and Felyx\ncould stay safe.
Yeah... I really am sorry, Xainfried.
It's all right, Amane. Your fears were\nmore than justified; that same tribe was\nresponsible for murdering my own.
What?! Goodness... What happened when\nyou met them, then?
We battled, for a time, and then went\nour separate ways.
Hold onâ€”how did neither of you kill\neach other?!
It was all thanks to Fydon and Felyx.
Even while they were being attacked,\nthey never lost sight of their mission\nas Saint Starfalls.
Fighting alone achieves nothingâ€”and\nit especially doesn't make for a welcoming\nworld.
Adults are quick to tell children to solve\ntheir disputes without violence, but what\nsort of example are we setting?
Wow... And the Syrols actually agreed?\nAmazing.
I'm glad you all made it through that.\nAnd while it may not be my place\nto say this...
Thank you for letting them live. They may\nbe dangerous and unruly at times, but\nthey are still my countrymen.
Of course. No one wants to lose those\nthey care about.
It can be easy to forget that. But to make\na world our children can enjoy, we must\npractice forgiveness, not hate alone.
So I swear this to you, Aegis: as the\nChild of Miracles, I will do all I can\nto aid your cause.
Are you sure? I would appreciate it,\nof course, but would your position\nallow it?
My goal is to stop dragons from causing\nhumanity any more pain.
But if all that means is humanity inflicting\nmore pain on itself, that doesn't solve\nanything.

Everyone wants a future their children can
live easily inâ€”a future free from sadness.
So if we all share a common goal, why
not work toward it together?
...I must admit, Amane, I'm quite taken\naback hearing that from you.
But thank you. It's very reassuring to\nknow I have your support.
It takes considerable courage to put past\ngrudges aside. You truly are a child of\nmiracles!
S-stop! No need to go overboard.
Oh! I almost forgot. I brought presents\nfor Fydon and Felyx.
I made some special dragon toys for\nthem to play with.
Yes, that was very nice of her indeed!\nWe should give her a present in return.\n...Hm?
We appear to be out of presents...
I'm so sorry! I assure you it's not because\nwe think you're some sort of naughty\nchildâ€”
Child?! Do not treat me like some infant!
Were we not conversing as adults mere\nmoments ago?!
Besides, you have already given me\nthe best present of all.
Your safe return. That's all I ever wanted.
(It can be hard to forsake hatred once\nit's taken root.)
(But I was given a chance to forgive those\nwho wronged me, and to join forces with\nAmane.)
